   :wanted "T,∇T,ΔT,drift must be QUERY-BACKED derived properties over typed edges (T(var)=1 iff no incident :coverage edge), NOT an ad-hoc ingestion pipeline like substrate-1's tension_surface"
   :discharged-by "geometric_layer_phase2.clj (compute-T / compute-grad / compute-laplacian / connected-components / jaccard drift), read-side over futon1a"}
  {:at :regression-equals-oracle-byte-for-byte
   :wanted "XTDB-derived geometry must EQUAL the fresh bb-v0.5 projection (paired-vars, coverage/call/vocab counts, top-±ΔT, drift hotspots, component sizes) AND be deterministic across re-runs"
   :discharged-by "phase_2_geometric_test.clj; required the distinct-qname L1-dedupe correction (bb over-counts duplicate defns — itself a real code-coherence finding)"}
  {:at :directed-edge-stable-id-collision
   :wanted ":calls src→dst and dst→src must NOT collide under the substrate-1 sorted-endpoint stable-ID scheme (hx:{type}:{sorted-endpoints})"
   :discharged-by "synthetic 3rd endpoint dir:src→dst (E-substrate-2-directed-edge-id); visible in every dumped edge id"}
  {:at :cross-codebase-counter-ratchet
   :wanted "a var qname shared across repos must not let a foreign ingest DECREASE another label's count (B-2: futon7 saw calls 128→100); per-type count is monotonic per repo"
